Software testing is a critical phase of the software development lifecycle. It involves the execution of a software component or system component to evaluate one or more properties of interest. The main goal of software testing is to identify errors, gaps or missing requirements in contrast to actual requirements.

There are several types of testing, including unit testing, integration testing, system testing, and acceptance testing. Each type of testing has its own purpose and is used at different stages of the development process.

For instance, JUnit is a popular testing tool for Java. Here's an example of a JUnit test case.

import org.junit.Test;
import static org.junit.Assert.assertEquals;

public class TestCalculator {
    @Test
    public void testAdd() {
        Calculator calculator = new Calculator();
        assertEquals(5, calculator.add(2, 3));
    }
}

