void bubbleSort(int arr[], int n) {
	for (int i = 0; i < n-1; i++)
		for (int j = 0; j < n-i-1; j++)
			if (arr[j] > arr[j+1])
				swap(&arr[j], &arr[j+1]);
}

Algorithms like these are the building blocks of software development. They're what make our programs do what we want them to do.

