In the realm of software development, the importance of efficient code cannot be overstated. Efficient code not only performs better but also makes the software easier to maintain and debug.

Take a look at this simple Java function that calculates the Fibonacci series:

public static void fibonacci(int n) {
	int a = 0, b = 1;
	for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
		int sum = a + b;
		a = b;
		b = sum;
	}
	return b;
}

This function calculates the nth Fibonacci number in O(n) time, which is a significant improvement over the naive recursive approach that takes O(2^n) time.

